{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Finish Jira hard-delete -> outbound re-create (replaces lost epic-3e36)\n\n## Why\nOn a Jira hard-delete the reconciler preserves local content (ADR 0027/0028) BUT never re-creates the Jira\nissue — a `follow_on` dict IS built (`apply_inbound.py:553-558`, `action=\"create_after_hard_delete\"`, shape\n`{direction, action, target, local_id}`) but never consumed, and the branch writes a COMMENT falsely claiming\nit was emitted. Finish the feature. Citations: `apply_inbound.py:541-560`; `applier.py:469-471` (consumer only\nhandles `kind==\"suppress_pair\"`).\n\n## What (one coherent path: inbound detect -> standard outbound CREATE mutation)\n1. Key mismatch: `_apply_inbound_delete` branches on `payload.get(\"probe_outcome\")` but the prod router emits\n   `reason`. CANONICAL = `reason`: update the branch; update BOTH affected fixtures (`test_inbound_leaf_bodies.py:333`\n   redirect case AND the hard_delete case).\n2. Consume the existing `action=\"create_after_hard_delete\"` follow-on. It carries `local_id` but NOT a `fields`\n   dict — and `create_one` (dispatch_one.py:227) REQUIRES `fields`. So the consumer must RECONSTRUCT `fields`:\n   look up the still-present LOCAL ticket by `local_id` (the hard-delete removed only the Jira side) and map it\n   via the SAME `_map_local_to_jira_fields` the outbound differ uses.\n3. Wiring (no typed-dispatch bypass, no mid-loop create_one): in the inbound consumer, build a STANDARD outbound\n   CREATE `Mutation` (with the reconstructed `fields`) and add it to the pass's outbound mutation list, so it flows\n   through the NORMAL outbound dispatch -> `create_one` (JQL dedup + `bind_pending`/`bind_confirm`). This is one\n   path (inbound produces an outbound create mutation; the standard batch applies it) — resolving the earlier\n   sentinel-vs-Mutation ambiguity.\n4. Idempotency: `create_one`'s JQL dedup + `recover_pending_bindings` prevent double-create on retry. If\n   `create_one` returns None because the per-pass REST-call budget is exhausted (`rest_calls >= _REST_CALL_BUDGET`),\n   the re-create DEFERS to the next pass (documented; same as the normal create path). Tests for both partial-failure\n   directions (create ok/rebind fails; create deferred/fails).\n5. Stale-binding lifecycle: `bind_confirm(local_id, new_key)` sets `bindings[local_id]=new_key` and adds\n   `reverse[new_key]` but does NOT remove `reverse[old_key]`. Explicitly delete the stale `reverse[old_key]` in the\n   same save — this edits `binding_store.py` (add to Scope). Test: local_id ends bound to new_key AND `reverse` has\n   no old_key entry.\n6. Guard: only genuine `hard_delete` re-creates (redirect/out_of_window/trash do NOT); guard test.\n7. Observability: log create + rebind success/failure. Fix the misleading COMMENT.\n8. Repoint `TODO(epic-3e36)` (apply_inbound.py:560) to THIS epic; clear `.joe-janitor/report-2026-07-02.md:137`.\n\n## Scope\n`apply_inbound.py` (reason key + keep the action follow-on), `applier.py` (consumer: reconstruct `fields`, emit\noutbound CREATE mutation), `binding_store.py` (reverse[old_key] cleanup), `dispatch_one.py` (via existing\n`create_one`), tests.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Canonical `reason` key; BOTH redirect + hard_delete fixtures updated; branch reachable in real dispatch.\n- [ ] Consumer reconstructs create `fields` from the local ticket (by local_id) via `_map_local_to_jira_fields`; emits a standard outbound CREATE mutation processed by the normal batch through `create_one` (no mid-loop call, no typed-dispatch bypass).\n- [ ] Idempotent: retry after either partial-failure direction does not double-create; REST-budget exhaustion defers to next pass (tests).\n- [ ] After re-create, local_id bound to NEW key AND stale `reverse[old_key]` removed in the same save (test).\n- [ ] Only genuine hard-deletes re-create (guard test); create/rebind logged; COMMENT accurate; TODO repointed; janitor flag cleared.\n- [ ] End-to-end test: inbound hard-delete -> outbound re-create in one pass.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783479635376679001,"uuid":"afb1096c-0f2e-4595-8371-de31a77e136c"}